019re There to Play a Sport,\u2019 Not \u2018Pop Off About Politics\u2019", "last_comment_created": 1770898932520, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 12, "score_up": 401, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"description": "Vice President JD Vance reminded Team USA athletes at the Olympics who have criticized the U.S., that they are there to \"represent\" the U.S.", "large_image": "tNs7HUuYISpABZc2.png", "title": "JD Vance to Olympic Athletes with 'Mixed Emotions': 'You're There to Play a Sport,' Not 'Pop Off About Politics'"}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ASFhTdklZ", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 66, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8415205, "raw_content": "Government should maintain electricity, water, roads, sanitation and borders.\n\nGovernment should not be a platform for enacting ideological social-experimentation. We should not know the names of anyone in government, because it is not supposed to be a celebrity-parade.\n\nThe JANITOR class got carried away and became 'rulers'. These fuckers don't rule us. We rule them. Get back in line JANITORS.\n\nThe government is supposed to be facilities-management. I never want to see another person from 'government' on TV or in the newspaper again. If they appear there, they've sufficiently fucked up their government role to be fired on the spot.\n\nI don't see my local-garage mechanic on TV. Why? Because he's not a fucking psychopath. He does his job so well that he does not need to broadcast how 'well' he's doing it.\n\nHe will die unknown, yet he will have done more to enrich America than anyone in our 'government'.\n\nThey've had more than a year to fix this. They've proven that they cannot.", "author": "infinite-lives", "created": 1770890160305, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "infinite-lives", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "TEAR IT ALL DOWN: Our government needs to be stripped down to nothing and built back at the relevant-points as infrastructure fails. This way we can turn it back into what it should be: Our janitors.\n", "last_comment_created": 1770896071867, "content": "<p>Government should maintain electricity, water, roads, sanitation and borders.</p>\n<p>Government should not be a platform for enacting ideological social-experimentation. We should not know the names of anyone in government, because it is not supposed to be a celebrity-parade.</p>\n<p>The JANITOR class got carried away and became 'rulers'. These fuckers don't rule us. We rule them. Get back in line JANITORS.</p>\n<p>The government is supposed to be facilities-management. I never want to see another person from 'government' on TV or in the newspaper again. If they appear there, they've sufficiently fucked up their government role to be fired on the spot.</p>\n<p>I don't see my local-garage mechanic on TV. Why? Because he's not a fucking psychopath. He does his job so well that he does not need to broadcast how 'well' he's doing it.</p>\n<p>He will die unknown, yet he will have done more to enrich America than anyone in our 'government'.</p>\n<p>They've had more than a year to fix this. They've proven that they cannot.</p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 2, "score_up": 66, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metad